modules.description: This module manages peer connections in a debugging setup, handling communication through asynchronous readers and writers. It provides functions to send and receive messages, track peer state, and manage connection lifecycles. Use it to coordinate interactions between a debugger and multiple debug targets over async I/O channels.

This module coordinates bidirectional communication between two peers in a debugging context, using asynchronous I/O. It allows intercepting and inspecting messages sent and received between peers, enabling real-time monitoring or modification of protocol traffic. It is used to implement man-in-the-middle debugging of protocol exchanges by wrapping and logging message flows between two connected endpoints.

This module manages peer connections in a debugging setup, providing functions to create, track, and communicate with connected peers. It works with peer objects that include a name, input reader, and output writer. Use this module to handle bidirectional communication between a debugger and target processes during debugging sessions.

This module facilitates man-in-the-middle debugging of protocol exchanges by coordinating bidirectional communication between two peers using asynchronous I/O. It enables interception, inspection, and logging of messages sent between connected endpoints, allowing real-time monitoring and modification of traffic. The module works with peer objects that include a name, input reader, and output writer, and is used to debug interactions between a debugger and target processes during active debugging sessions.
